item.title: Neurotoxin - Vulture
item.dc:creator: iammane
item.description:
What is that “Ha” sound in there? I heard it twice. That is awesome.

Okay, aaaand we’re back. First off, I love how the piano plays off the regular trap style synths and what not. I really like the glitchy broken up part. 1) It totally fits the title of the song and 2) Even if the song was called something else I’d STILL like it. These are the kinds of production choices people are going to be divided on no matter what.

Listening a third time.

This melody is going to be stuck in my head I have a feeling. That “Ha” sound I was talking about is around 1:01, with headphones on now I can tell it’s just something automating but it’s still hella cool.

Honestly can’t think of anything I would change. Liked and reposted

Ayy! Nice track! Here’s some feedback

Intro: nice chords, I think there’s a weird tone thing going on there. It’s a little too punchy, I think a decrease in lowpass would be awesome.

Love the snares at 0:20!

0:40: Whoa, funky stuff going on! I’m not a big fan of this sorta sound but it’s pretty dank. Some bass?

1:17: This is awesome!

Overall great track! Chorus is my fav part.
